{"id":"d=origam-topic-249//p=b2f7df22b67f46dd98c612c58eb82a6f","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-249"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["9704cdde44a643a8973cb9313aab3993"],"__file_part":["f5c2cc0903034278bd8d150b146ee098"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"category":["docs"],"categoryId":["8"],"topicId":["249"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/contributing-to-github-repositories/249"],"title":["Contributing to GitHub repositories"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# Contributing to GitHub repositories\n\nCategory: docs\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/contributing-to-github-repositories/249\n\n@tvavrda (2016-07-18 09:08:34Z):\n Sometimes you fix something or create an enhancement you think would be beneficial to everyone of us. That is great and this is the correct way to do it: by  Forking  on GitHub and creating a  Pull Request . \n \n Fork a repository \n \n \n When you do some changes in our code, do not send us updated files. Instead go to our GitHub repository and press the  Fork  button on top. \n          Sn\u00EDmek obrazovky 2016-07-18 v 10.45.44.png  2034\u00D7232 25.3 KB         \n This will create  your own version of our repository . \n \n Commit Changes \n \n \n Then do the changes you want using  Git Client  or just upload the files manually to GitHub like this: \n          Sn\u00EDmek obrazovky 2016-07-18 v 10.40.29.png  2016\u00D7400 42.9 KB         \n Enter all descriptions so you and us know exactly what was fixed and why. In case you are not proficient with Git, just commit the changes to the  master  branch. \n          Sn\u00EDmek obrazovky 2016-07-18 v 10.40.20.png  1487\u00D7693 44.1 KB         \n \n Create a Pull request \n \n \n After this GitHub will notify you that you did some changes that we do not have in our main repository and that you can create a Pull request. Press the  Pull request  button. \n          Sn\u00EDmek obrazovky 2016-07-18 v 10.36.43.png  2092\u00D7478 53.2 KB         \n Check that  Able to merge  is there (otherwise you are too far behind our own changes in the affected files and you will have to solve the conflicts first. Then click on  Create pull request  button. \n          Sn\u00EDmek obrazovky 2016-07-18 v 10.37.12.png  2048\u00D7654 68.6 KB         \n Finalize the request by checking the descriptions and pressing again on  Create pull request  button. You can check on top you can see that you are actually requesting a pull from your to our main repository. \n          Sn\u00EDmek obrazovky 2016-07-18 v 10.37.32.png  1678\u00D71180 109 KB         \n   Done \n Now you successfully created a request we will see. After that we will be able to review your changes and merge them into our own repository. Also the commit will be forever assigned to you so everybody will know who was responsible for this bug fix/feature.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-04-29T00:23:40"},"vector":[-0.0057282923,-0.036655,0.015009961,0.020625705,0.011436573,-0.026768826,0.022886291,-0.03065274,-0.017062359,0.0014406472,0.02199037,0.022433272,-0.021784436,0.0371141,0.008756216,-0.0063596717,-0.011028555,0.010925759,0.0070990063,-0.018788854,0.026374916,-0.005415571,0.037602346,0.00027308165,0.047237232,-0.0044600368,-0.0046090926,-0.009570656,0.03857773,-0.03810353,0.009493941,-0.030444,0.013691818,-0.06230762,-0.049057238,-0.02127523,-0.0010944271,-0.04759925,-0.0051847827,0.0051917555,-0.01982494,-0.009080168,0.011827608,-0.03680012,-0.00012968465,-0.02375421,-0.0012063916,-0.0008395268,0.01304276,-0.0060274363,-0.0124246115,-0.01529684,0.04310726,-0.018845191,0.001728825,0.05813134,-0.012570727,0.010762573,-0.046153814,-0.03219085,-0.02705353,0.012644228,-0.05808767,-0.0018127026,0.020580905,0.052499674,-0.013954675,0.007494514,-0.011518656,-0.021304931,-0.017804444,0.014246586,-0.02067744,-0.031020295,-0.022108808,-0.0069149057,0.001